node.text:
This week, instead of sipping, we’re snacking. Contributing editor Sean Flynn (@travelingnewyorker) is back in Riviera Nayarit, Mexico at One&Only Mandarina (@oomandarina) cooking with Executive Chef Olivier Deboise (@olideboise). Chef’s Fire-Roasted Gratinated Oysters are sure to be a hit at your next summer party.
.
Ingredients:
½ dozen oysters
1 ½ oz butter
1 ½ oz aged goat cheddar
½ tsp shallots, diced
½ tsp Serrano chili, chopped
½ tsp epazote, julienned
Zest of 1 lemon
Zest of 1 lime 
.
Top each oyster with ¼ oz of butter and divide the chopped ingredients, lemon zest, and lime zest among the oysters. Top with grated aged goat cheddar. Grill over a medium to low flame for three to four minutes and brûlée for one and a half minutes. Serve hot.

node.title: These Fire-Roasted Oysters Are the Perfect Summer Appetizer

node.text: Next up on Sipping With, Sean (@travelingnewyorker) visits One&Only Mandarina (@oomandarina) in beautiful Riviera Nayarit, Mexico, where Mixologist Ivan Aguilar shows us how to make one of his favorite cocktails. Of course, no trip to Mexico is complete without tequila, so naturally, that’s our spirit of choice for this episode. In fact, Ivan shows us that tequila can be used to add a twist to cocktails that traditionally use other liquors. We hope you’ll follow along and sip with us at home. Cheers!

node.title: Calling All Tequila Lovers, This Cocktail Could Become Your New Favorite

node.text: On the latest episode of Sipping With, Sean (@travelingnewyorker) heads to his hometown of Buffalo, New York to learn how to make three different summertime cocktails from head bartender at Lloyd Taco Factory (@lloydtacofactory), Jon Wheelock (@jwheels1). We won't give away what they're making, but we will say, if gin is your spirit of choice, you're in for a treat. We hope you’ll follow along and sip with us at home. Cheers!

node.title: Elevate Your Next Summer Get-together With These Cocktail Recipes

node.text: Introducing Sipping With, a new series hosted by Contributing Editor Sean Flynn (@travelingnewyorker), who’s taking us behind the bar at world-renowned restaurants, hotels, and resorts to see how the best in the business craft specialty cocktails. Cheers!

node.title: Learn How One of the Best Hotels in NYC Makes Its Signature Margarita

node.text: In this new video series, Walk With T+L, we'll be taking you on some of the best walking tours across the globe. On this episode: the island of Amorgos, Greece. The Greek Islands are on just about everyone's bucket list. But like many of the world’s most photogenic destinations, over-tourism has become a real issue. Luckily, there are more than 200 inhabited islands in Greece, meaning you can get all of the beauty and none the crowds on some of the lesser-known islands, like Amorgos. Come along! node.title: This Greek Island Has All of the Beauty and None of the Crowds

node.text: In this new video series, Walk With T+L, we'll be taking you on some of the best walking tours across the globe. On this episode: Paris, France. A city that needs no introduction, Paris may as well be synonymous with food, culture, fashion, and architecture. Despite being a bucket-list destination for millions of people, the French capital still holds plenty of hidden secrets beyond the Eiffel Tower and world-class museums. Join us on this walking tour to see for yourself. Tour by @walkstours

node.title: Jet Off to Paris From the Comfort of Your Home on This Virtual Walking Tour

These stories will give insight into the historic work of the Underground Railroad and the experiences of the individuals who traveled it in hopes of escaping slavery. Come along. Tour by @manumissiontour

node.text: In this new video series, Walk With T+L, we'll be taking you on some of the best walking tours across the globe. On this episode: The Holiday Tour of New York City. In a normal year, millions of visitors would be traveling to the Big Apple to see it decked out for the holiday season. This year, however, most of those visitors will be staying home, which is why we decided to bring New York City’s holiday cheer to you. Join us as we visit the Rockefeller Christmas Tree, Radio City Music Hall, and more. Happy holidays! Tour by @topdogtoursnyc

node.title: Stuck at Home This Christmas? Join Us on the Holiday Tour of New York City

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Travel + Leisure on August 19, 2021. May be an image of furniture, tree, mountain, snow and text that says '13 Ways to Save Money on Hotels During the Holiday Season * 我'.

node.text: The November and December holidays can be a wonderful time for visiting friends and family, but they can also be a challenging season for your wallet. Luckily, there are ways to save if you plan ahead and spend strategically. Get 13 tips for saving on hotels this holiday season at the link in bio. ❄️

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Travel + Leisure in Italy with @chrisroams. May be an image of nature.

node.text: To travel to the Dolomites, the Alpine mountain range strung between two northern Italian provinces, is to become immersed in a wholly unique destination. Planning a trip? At the link in bio, our travel guide will point you to the can’t-miss sights and activities among these majestic peaks. #tlpicks courtesy of @chrisroams

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Travel + Leisure in Zanzibar, Tanzania with @nomadicfare. May be an image of ocean and nature.

node.text: Zanzibar is consistently voted as one of the top islands in Africa and the Middle East by T+L readers, and it's not hard to see why. Get the full list of the best islands in the region at the link in bio. #tlpicks courtesy of @nomadicfare

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Travel + Leisure on August 18, 2021. node.text:
This week on Let's Go Together, guest host Nina Ruggiero (@ninamarienyc), T+L’s Deputy Editor, sits down with winemaker Denise Adams, who has vineyards in both California and France, to talk about the joys and challenges of making wine in two of the most well-known winemaking regions in the world.
.
Click the link in bio to listen on Apple Podcasts, or listen wherever you get your podcasts.

node.text: When it comes to staying in a hotel, there are some definitive dos and don’ts to follow that will make your travels even more enjoyable. Get our list of the 10 biggest mistakes to avoid when checking into and out of a hotel at the link in bio.

node.text: National parks get all the attention, but some of the country's most beautiful landscapes are found in lesser-known (and noticeably less busy) state parks. Get our list of the best state park in every U.S. state at the link in bio. #tlpicks courtesy of @v_outdoors

node.text: There's a monumental beauty to the Faroes, a chain of 18 volcanic islands in the North Atlantic between Norway, Scotland, and Iceland. Get our guide to the perfect long weekend on the isles at the link in bio. #tlpicks courtesy of @chrisroams

node.text: London has acquired an unfair reputation for bland food, when in fact, diversity and high quality local produce are boosting its ever-growing food scene. Even better, the city’s magical aesthetic often translates into restaurant decor that will renew your sense of wonder. Get our list of everything you need to eat on your next trip to London at the link in bio. #tlpicks courtesy of @gulshanlondon
